{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented a snapshot-backed workspace shell with a real `GET /api/v1/sessions/{id}` route, a responsive 1:2 chat/canvas layout, a compact stage/save-status header, and proper loading/error states. The code checkpoint is committed on th...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_93", "text": "Implemented a snapshot-backed workspace shell with a real `GET /api/v1/sessions/{id}` route, a responsive 1:2 chat/canvas layout, a compact stage/save-status header, and proper loading/error states. The code checkpoint is committed on the current branch as `5bd32f5` (`feat(prompt-22): workspace two pane layout`), and the required reviewer summary is at [22-workspace-two-pane-layout.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.summary.md).\n\nVerification ran cleanly for the touched areas: `python -m pytest backend/tests/test_session_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py`, `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, and `npm run test`. Browser QA captured [prompt-22-workspace-desktop.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-22-workspace-desktop.png) and [prompt-22-workspace-mobile.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-22-workspace-mobile.png); the desktop chat pane measured `0.328` of the shell width, and mobile stacked cleanly. The only verification limit was a pre-existing compose backend blocker from the local `secrets.yaml` schema, so the browser run used intercepted API responses against the live Vite app instead of a fully live backend container.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 175, "prompt_index": 23, "prompt_name": "22 \u2014 Workspace Two-Pane Layout", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T02:05:06-07:00"}
